------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Rails application folder structure

a) App - contains Model, View, Controller, Assets, helper, Mailer
b) Bin - contains code to start, setup, update, deploy and run
c) Config - routes, database and other configurations
d) Config.ru - rack configuration to start rack based application
e) Db - database migration files
f) Gemfile/Gemfile.lock - gem dependencies required for application
g) Lib - extended modules
h) Log - application log
i) Public - static files
j) Rakefile - load task that can be run from command line
k) Test - contains unit testing code
l) Tmp - temporary files
m) Vendor - third party code

